5.    If you play an instrument - bring it along.  

6.    If you don't have transportation, call John for the shuttle schedule - they will drop you off at our parking lot and pick you up the next day or so?  I don't know how they run on weekends, call John and he will give you the numbers of the shuttles that go from Prescott to Phoenix and back.  John is at the Creekside  928  632-0777

7.    If you need a ride and can't make the  shuttle, email me and I will try to find you a ride with someone who is driving up.


For those who come up Saturday evening, we can decorate the lodge Great Room and the Cryomas Tree and if it is not too cold we can have a bon fire at the fire pit area.  Bring your jacket and scarf just in case.

Don't be shy if you have never been to a cryofeast, they are a social gathering just like going home for the holidays.  

You don't have to live in Arizona to attend.   

Look forward to seeing old friends and making new ones.

David, Trudy and John.






